    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThere are a few conditions when colorscheme flickers when launching neovim. By flickering I mean that it between changin background from terminal background to neovim background, there is a period of time when the background is black.\r\n\r\nI think it is somewhat related to #19362 . These only reproduce on nightly, 0.9.5 is fine.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nFor any of this, run `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua` with the contents of `minimal.lua` described below.\r\n\r\n#### termguicolors\r\n\r\n\r\nAfter setting `termguicolor`, background switches to black before switching to the user-defined one. Run with `sleep` to pause on black background, or with some synchronous code to see flickering.\r\n\r\nI know that `termguicolors` is enabled automatically in 0.10, however this causes 0.9 configs to flicker and people waste time debugging. Also, I don't know how this works under the hood, but automatic setting of `termguicolors` seems to happen after `init.lua` is loaded, because `vim.o.termguicolors` returns `false` if printed inside user config (when not set manually).\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.termguicolors = true\r\n-- vim.cmd.sleep(1)\r\nvim.fn.system(\"notify-send loading\")\r\n\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme(\"blue\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### VimEnter\r\n\r\nIf you have a VimEnter autocommand with any synchronous action, the same thing happens. There are 3 cases. \r\n\r\nIf you run (1) - you will see the same effect as with `termguicolors` - background switches to black. \r\nIf you run (2) - you may see very subtle flickering of the screen. I choose `fn.system` as a generic synchronous side-effect. The same happens with `system():wait`.\r\nIf you run (3) - no flickering. The same is described in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19362#issuecomment-1924993842\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"VimEnter\", {\r\n\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\t--[[ (1) ]] vim.cmd.sleep(1)\r\n\t\t--[[ (2) ]] vim.fn.system(\"notify-send vimenter\")\r\n\t\t--[[ (3) ]] vim.print(\"asdf\")\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme(\"blue\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### unnamedplus\r\n\r\nSame flickering, however you cannot pause on it by running `sleep`, maybe it happens at different point in time. But, if you run synchronous commands, then you can see the flickering.\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.clipboard = \"unnamedplus\"\r\nvim.fn.system(\"notify-send loading\")\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme(\"blue\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo flickering like on 0.9.5. \r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.10.0-dev-3097+g064f3e42e\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux/X11\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nTested on: kitty + tmux; kitty; wezterm; alacritty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nRespectively^: tmux-256color; xterm-kitty; xterm-256color; alacritty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nBuild from repo",
