            "body": "Bisected to 037ea6e786b5d05f4a8965e4c2ba6aa60ec7c01a. cc @luukvbaal \r\n\r\n**EDIT:** Hmm there might be more than one thing going on here. Using this as init.lua:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"VimEnter\", {\r\n\tcallback = function()\r\n\t\t--[[ (1) ]] vim.cmd.sleep(1)\r\n\t\t--[[ (2) ]] vim.fn.system(\"notify-send vimenter\")\r\n\t\t--[[ (3) ]] vim.print(\"asdf\")\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\nvim.cmd.colorscheme(\"blue\")\r\n```\r\n\r\nand running with `VIMRUNTIME=runtime build/bin/nvim --clean -u init.lua`, the black screen occurs on https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/8bb5089974e14f043a0b0c17e4d38dbd0b9a9ab2 as well. But when starting Nvim \"normally\" (i.e. with my own init.vim), I don't see any flicker on 8bb5089974e14f043a0b0c17e4d38dbd0b9a9ab2 or any following commit, until  037ea6e786b5d05f4a8965e4c2ba6aa60ec7c01a.\r\n\r\nWill open a separate issue for this.",
